Maxima nodded. "Those skills need to be honed in. Your programming would 
enhance that." 

She stood straight. "You are a Predacon, a Decepticon decendent," in some 
ways, a decendent of her & her comrades. "You are NOT a beast, but an 
instrument of destruction. Some Predacons have perhaps lost the devotion it 
took to be a Decepticon. I'm NOT a beast, Blackstorm. I am a Decepticon. 
Unfortunately, in some Predacon lookalike form." She was more speaking about 
the Predacons she once knew. Their animalistic fury was famous. But the 
majority of these so called Predacons made the name sake a joke. She would 
rather be known as a Decepticon. For that is what she still is.

Motioning for Blackstorm to come to her, "Stop trying to 'think'. Access your 
data banks & files. If you are a Predacon or Decepticon, you will function 
more as a bot, a true Cybertronian. Not some pathetic organic beast." 

--part1_181.19ff9242.2bd8e560_boundary
